<Category category="Oil Temperature Indicators" slug="transformer-oil-temperature-indicators" title="Transformer Oil Temperature Indicators | INNO" description="Compare INNO BWY2, BWY-802/803 and BWY-D804AITH transformer oil temperature indicators for top-oil measurement, cooling control and remote output." heading="Transformer Oil Temperature Indicators" intro="Measure and control the top-oil temperature of an oil-immersed transformer with local indication, adjustable contacts and remote signal options." definition="An oil temperature indicator, or OTI, senses transformer oil temperature at a thermometer pocket, usually in the top-oil region. It can display the value locally and operate contacts for cooling or alarm functions." />
